    "This is mainly due to the fact that it requires many years of education and training, and it is a career that saves lives and contributes greatly to the health and wellbeing of the community.",
    "It's also considered that they usually earn a high salary which adds to its prestige.",
    "Nonetheless, certain diversities within UK population that may place lesser value on higher education or that prioritize other types of careers could somewhat lower this score from a perfect 100.\"",
    "\"Cardiologists play a critical role in maintaining public health by diagnosing and treating heart diseases, which are some of the major causes of morbidity and mortality in the UK.",
    "Therefore, their occupation holds a high level of social value."
